-- Egypt's Pioneers Holding plans capital increase to help finance Rooya acquisition
-- By Shadia Nasralla and Stephen Kalin
-- Thu Apr 24, 2014 02:15PM EDT
-- None



CAIRO, April 24 (Reuters) - Pioneers Holding <PIOH.CA> plans to use a capital increase to help finance the acquisition of a 60 percent stake in real estate investment firm Rooya Group, one of the firm's senior executives said.

"The deal will be financed in cash and through a capital increase in Pioneers Holding shares subject to valuation,"  Mohamed Aboulghait, managing director, financial services, told Reuters in an interview.